MsmqIntegrationSecurityMode Enum

Definition

MsmqIntegrationSecurityMode is an enumeration that specifies the security modes supported by the MSMQ integration channel.

In this Article

public enum MsmqIntegrationSecurityMode
Inheritance
Object
ValueType
System.Enum
MsmqIntegrationSecurityMode

Remarks

This enumeration can be set within a configuration file in the <security> section. It can also be set in code by passing the appropriate value into the constructor of the MsmqIntegrationBinding class.

Fields

None

No security.
Transport

Use the MSMQ transport security.
